Game Boy Color RPG Vision Document

Project Vision:
Create a retro-style RPG game that captures the essence and technical constraints of Game Boy Color games from the late 1990s and early 2000s. This project aims to develop a complete role-playing game with classic gameplay mechanics, authentic visual and audio aesthetics, and modern development practices.

Core Objectives:
1. Authentic GBC Experience - Recreate the look, feel, and technical limitations of original Game Boy Color hardware
2. Complete RPG Systems - Implement classic RPG mechanics including turn-based combat, character progression, inventory management, and quest systems
3. Engaging Narrative - Develop an immersive story with memorable characters and meaningful player choices
4. Technical Excellence - Use modern development tools while respecting retro constraints

Target Audience:
- Retro gaming enthusiasts who appreciate classic RPG gameplay
- Developers interested in constraint-based game development
- Players seeking nostalgic gaming experiences with modern polish

Key Features:
- Turn-based combat system with tactical depth
- Character progression with multiple classes/paths
- Inventory and equipment management
- Quest system with main story and side quests
- Authentic GBC visual style (160x144 resolution, limited color palette)
- Chiptune soundtrack reminiscent of classic GBC games
- Save/load functionality
- Multiple towns, dungeons, and explorable areas

Technical Constraints:
- Resolution: 160x144 pixels
- Color palette: 56 colors maximum on screen, 32,768 total colors available
- Sprite limitations: 40 sprites maximum, 10 per scanline
- Audio: 4 sound channels (2 pulse wave, 1 wave, 1 noise)
- Memory constraints simulated for authentic feel

Success Criteria:
- Playable demo with at least 2-3 hours of gameplay
- Complete combat and progression systems
- Authentic visual and audio presentation
- Stable performance and bug-free core mechanics
- Positive feedback from retro gaming community

Long-term Vision:
This project serves as both a tribute to classic Game Boy Color RPGs and a learning exercise in constraint-based game development. Success will be measured by the game's ability to evoke nostalgia while providing engaging modern gameplay experiences.